Add a comprehensive code coverage reporting system to the Forever library. Create `scripts/coverage.js` that generates detailed coverage reports for all tests. Requirements: 1) Use Node.js built-in `--coverage` flag or integrate with `c8`/`nyc` coverage library. 2) Generate reports in multiple formats: HTML, JSON, and text. 3) Add coverage thresholds configuration in package.json (minimum 80% line coverage, 70% branch coverage, 90% function coverage). 4) Create a `coverage` directory to store reports. 5) Add a `"coverage"` script to package.json that runs `node scripts/coverage.js`. 6) The script should fail if coverage thresholds are not met. 7) Add a `--watch` mode for continuous coverage monitoring during development. 8) Generate a coverage badge (SVG) that can be added to README.md. 9) Write tests in `tests/coverage.test.js` that verify the coverage reporting functionality works correctly. 10) Add integration with the existing changelog generator to include coverage statistics in release notes.